# Commit Message Template for AegisX Platform
# 
# Format: type(scope): description
#
# Type: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore, perf
# Scope: Optional, component/module affected  
# Description: Brief description in present tense

# Examples:
# feat(auth): add user authentication system
# fix(api): resolve user creation endpoint issue
# docs(readme): update installation instructions
# refactor(database): optimize user queries
# perf(frontend): implement lazy loading for components

# üö® FORBIDDEN PATTERNS (will trigger v2.x.x releases):
# ‚ùå BREAKING CHANGE:
# ‚ùå BREAKING CHANGES:
# ‚ùå BREAKING:

# ‚úÖ SAFE ALTERNATIVES for significant changes:
# ‚úÖ IMPORTANT: for significant changes requiring attention
# ‚úÖ MAJOR UPDATE: for substantial feature changes
# ‚úÖ SIGNIFICANT: for notable modifications
# ‚úÖ API CHANGE: for API modifications maintaining compatibility
# ‚úÖ MIGRATION: for database or configuration changes
# ‚úÖ DEPRECATED: for marking features as deprecated

# Additional guidelines:
# - Use present tense ("add" not "added")
# - Keep first line under 50 characters
# - Add detailed description in body if needed
# - Reference issues/PRs: "fixes #123", "closes #456"
#
# Project maintains v1.x.x versioning only
# Major version v2.x.x releases are FORBIDDEN